    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-weight:bold;">Abbreviations</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Abbreviations are the common ones in German English Dutch.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">If you use Joh for John or Mat for Matthew. Consider that you need three letters at least.For abbreviations it is an exceptions then Jn works for John.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">For books with numbers like 1 Corinthians, etc, important is that there is a space after the number and the first letter of the book.</para>
